    "narrative": "For April 26, the Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is headlined by **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (78.13), **James Wood** (75.23), and **Corbin Carroll** (72.54). **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Arrighetti, whose high xERA (5.10) and slow delivery provide a perfect storm for stolen base opportunities, which we have heavily weighted. Similarly, **James Wood** is in a prime spot to produce; despite facing a lefty, his leadoff placement (+10%) and the soft matchup against Hudson boost his floor substantially. **Corbin Carroll** remains an elite start, as his xwOBA profile and leadoff-style output from the three-hole create consistent value against King.\n\nStrategic selection today highlights the importance of matching platoon advantages with volume. **Tyler Soderstrom** (69.65) and **Brice Turang** (57.33) are locked in as core contributors, with **Brice Turang** seeing a major uptick due to his leadoff role. While **Seiya Suzuki** (50.07) and **Mickey Moniak** (50.33) hover near our marginal threshold, they remain active to ensure we maximize our daily game caps. **Kyle Karros** (33.84) stands as the most notable bench decision; he was pushed out of the lineup due to a brutal matchup against McLean, whose low xERA (3.04) and the disadvantageous wind-in conditions rendered **Kyle Karros** a sub-floor asset. \n\nWe are exercising caution with **Vinnie Pasquantino** (41.10) and **Dalton Rushing** (47.04), both of whom are facing difficult left-handed arms. **Vinnie Pasquantino** is hindered by the dynamic platoon penalty against Detmers, while **Dalton Rushing** is relegated to the bottom of the order and facing the elite Imanaga. We will be monitoring the weather and potential lineup adjustments for **Luis Campusano** closely, as his utility spot remains the most volatile piece of today\u2019s puzzle. Our priority remains capturing the league-scarcest stolen base production, and as such, we are comfortable taking the slightly lower aggregate projection on some bats to keep our high-speed threats active.",
